<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="types">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Types.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Holotype:</emphasis>
♂ (IZCAS), Indonesia, Sulawesi, mountain in Palopo, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="2" direction="south" minutes="59.9210" orientation="latitude" precision="1" value="-2.9986835">2°59.9210'S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="120" direction="east" minutes="08.5650" orientation="longitude" precision="1" value="120.14275">120°08.5650'E</geoCoordinate>
, 465 m, 2.IX.2017, H. Liu &amp; Z. Chen. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Paratype</emphasis>
: 1♀ (IZCAS), same data as holotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">The species name is an adjective referring to the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
Males of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. palopoensis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palopoensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. palopoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be distinguished from all other species of the genus by the swollen ovate shape of the bulb bearing a short embolus distally (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Psiloderces palopoensis sp. nov., male holotype. A Palp, ventral view B bulb, ventral view C palp, prolateral view D palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: CP = cymbial protrusion, EM = embolus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.902.38967.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/370859" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">15B</figureCitation>
), 5 times shorter than the length of the tegulum (vs. absence of the extreme length difference of the embolus and tegulum in congeners), and relatively pale color of the male and female; female can be distinguished by widely separated, short, digitiform spermathecae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Psiloderces palopoensis sp. nov., male holotype and female paratype. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.902.38967.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/370858" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">14A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Male</emphasis>
(Holotype). Total length 1.41; carapace 0.55 long, 0.63 wide; abdomen 0.86 long, 0.50 wide. Carapace round and pale brown, with trident brown stripes medially and brown patches laterally (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Psiloderces palopoensis sp. nov., male holotype and female paratype. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.902.38967.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/370858" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">14C</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae pale brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 29" captionStartId="F29" captionText="Figure 29. Cheliceral retromargin, posterior view. A Psiloderces penajamensis sp. nov. B P. malinoensis sp. nov. C P. palopoensis sp. nov. D P. grohotensis sp. nov. E P. bolang sp. nov. Abbreviations: CL = cheliceral laminar, RT = retromargin teeth." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.902.38967.figure29" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/370873" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">29C</figureCitation>
). Clypeus slanting, purplish. Endites purplish, light brown basally. Labium purplish, delimiting pair of light brown circular dots. Sternum purplish. Abdomen elongated, dorsum with indistinct dark brown pattern posteriorly, antero-ventrally brown with semi-circular patch, posterior with dark brown pattern delimiting light brown dotted vertical lines laterally and V-shaped medially. Legs uniformly brown; measurements: I 5.72 (0.55, 0.16, 1.88, 2.13, 1.00), II 5.78 (1.60, 0.20, 1.60, 1.63, 0.75), III missing, IV 8.33 (2.19, 0.25, 2.60, 2.20, 1.09). Palp (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Psiloderces palopoensis sp. nov., male holotype. A Palp, ventral view B bulb, ventral view C palp, prolateral view D palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: CP = cymbial protrusion, EM = embolus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.902.38967.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/370859" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">15A-D</figureCitation>
): femur slender, 5 times longer than patella; patella not swollen; tibia 2 times shorter than femur; cymbium almost as wide and long as tibia, with protrusion; bulb pale brown, bulging ovate with embolus arising distally; embolus thinly, sheet-liked, 5 times shorter than entire length of tegulum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Psiloderces palopoensis sp. nov., male holotype. A Palp, ventral view B bulb, ventral view C palp, prolateral view D palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: CP = cymbial protrusion, EM = embolus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.902.38967.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/370859" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">15B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Female</emphasis>
(Paratype). General features and coloration similar to those of male (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Psiloderces palopoensis sp. nov., male holotype and female paratype. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.902.38967.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/370858" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">14D, E</figureCitation>
). Measurements: total length 1.49; carapace 0.55 long, 0.60 wide; abdomen 0.94 long, 0.55 wide. Leg measurements: I 8.27 (2.19, 0.20, 2.50, 2.25, 1.13), II 6.28 (1.75, 0.25, 1.65, 1.75, 0.88), III 4.30 (1.30, 0.20, 1.40, 1.20, 0.20), IV 6.91 (1.88, 0.23, 2.00, 1.80, 1.00). Endogyne (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Psiloderces palopoensis sp. nov., male holotype and female paratype. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.902.38967.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/370858" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">14A</figureCitation>
): widely spaced, digitiform spermathecae, ratio of length of spermatheca and the interdistance of digitiform spermathecae -1:10 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Psiloderces palopoensis sp. nov., male holotype and female paratype. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.902.38967.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/370858" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">14A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
